<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-05T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-05T07:00:00-05:00" n="383" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5531/805: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-05T13:00:00+01:00">September 5, 1939—1
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 5—9 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>117. The Foreign Office has inquired whether the Embassy has received
                                any information regarding the Department’s plans for trade agreement
                                negotiations in view of present political situation in Europe;
                                inquiry was also made as to where these negotiations would be held.
                                Please reply by cable.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>